msgctxt "mn72:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 72 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 72 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn72:0.2"
msgid "Aggivacchasutta "
msgstr "With Vacchagotta on Fire "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, pts-vp-pli1.484, sc1
msgctxt "mn72:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn72:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn72:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho vacchagotto paribbājako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Then the wanderer Vacchagotta went up to the Buddha and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "mn72:1.4"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3, sc2
msgctxt "mn72:3.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu kho, bho gotama, ‘sassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti—"
msgstr "“Master Gotama, is this your view: ‘The world is eternal. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly’?” "

#. VAR: evaṃdiṭṭhi → evaṃdiṭṭhī (bj, s2, s3, km, mr)
msgctxt "mn72:3.2"
msgid "evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavaṃ gotamo”ti? "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn72:3.3"
msgid "“Na kho ahaṃ, vaccha, evaṃdiṭṭhi: "
msgstr "“That’s not my view, Vaccha.” "

msgctxt "mn72:3.4"
msgid "‘sassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti. "
msgstr " "

